# Property Rules

## Purpose
Property inventory, media, SEO per `docs/PRD.md` 4.3, BR-P*, `docs/SEO_STRATEGY.md`.

## Requirements
- Slug unique per tenant; auto-generate from title BR-P01.
- Public listing: status=available, is_public=true, ≥1 image BR-P02.
- On sold/rented: remove from ES within 60s BR-P03.
- S3 presigned upload flow; WebP thumbnails async.
- Elasticsearch sync via BullMQ on publish/update.
- Public API exposes slug-based URLs only for client role.
- Bulk CSV max 500 rows with error report BR-P05.

## Restrictions
- Archived properties reject new inquiries BR-P07.
- Sales executive cannot delete properties.
- No public index for draft/sold listings.

## Best Practices
- SSR/ISR public pages with schema.org RealEstateListing.
- Primary assignment max one per property BR-P06.
- INR price formatting; store decimal in DB.

## Anti-Patterns
- Sync ES in HTTP request handler.
- UUID in public URL path.

## Examples

```typescript
if (dto.is_public) {
  await this.validatePublicReady(property); // images + status
  await this.searchQueue.add('index_property', { tenantId, propertyId });
}
```
